yeah this is from the dot see this interesting just to tell me a little bit about who the source is to lighthouse because i don't think you've told me yeah well who this person is and how this all this material happened to be in the possession of the person obviously nobody knew anything about obviously we're going to get through all that yeah um phyllis armstrong was the daughter of jane and jane armstrong the stepdaughter of richard armstrong um and

12:32.048 --> 12:43.498
Richard really was the collector of the family, I understand from, I've talked to both Jane, no, Jane's dad, I've talked to Phyllis, who's now in her 60s, at the time she was 17 when she talked from the bell tolls.

12:44.419 --> 12:49.164
The stuff basically resided in her closet for 50 years.

12:50.004 --> 12:52.607
She moved from Washington, D.C.

12:52.707 --> 13:01.515
to North Carolina in 87, and her son came up from Florida to help him move, and they came across this stuff, and the son

13:01.715 --> 13:05.419
you know, talks Mom out of some of it.

13:05.439 --> 13:09.863
He then goes back to Florida and walks into the book dealer's shop.

13:11.104 --> 13:19.773
The long process of two and a half months, three months, culminates in my getting some of the stuff, not the greatest stuff, but some of the stuff from the son.

13:21.014 --> 13:25.678
And when I'm in Florida, from the son's house, I call Phyllis on the phone.

13:27.120 --> 13:30.683
She's in North Carolina by now, or I don't know whether she moved from Washington, D.C.

13:30.843 --> 13:31.384
to North Carolina.

13:31.735 --> 14:00.493
by then, but in any case, every time I talked to her, I asked her if there was any more, you know, any Christmas cards or anything, and she never said there was, but when I got back to California with these six inscribed articles and a short story, I wrote her a long letter, you know, acknowledging what wonderful material it was, and again, asking if there was any more, and I didn't, this was, it would have been probably December of 87,

14:02.144 --> 14:06.108
And I got a letter six months later in June.

14:06.188 --> 14:07.590
Six months.

14:07.610 --> 14:11.674
And she said, basically it was, he has to do that some more and I'll give it to my daughter.

14:13.036 --> 14:16.219
And it turns out the daughter and the son don't speak.

14:16.239 --> 14:19.482
They live in the same small boy town and they don't speak.

14:20.163 --> 14:28.472
So I then phoned Phyllis and asked if it would be appropriate for me to contact the daughter directly.

14:28.688 --> 14:29.269
Well, yes.

14:29.289 --> 14:38.983
By implication, I think the daughter learned that the son got a lot of money for the stuff, and Mom had given the rest of the stuff to the daughter, so... A lot of money from you.

14:39.044 --> 14:47.516
A lot of money from me to the son, and so the daughter learned that what she had was very valuable, and, you know, let's contact Mr. Neekin, so Phyllis wrote the letters to me.

14:47.536 --> 14:49.039
