15:33.695 --> 15:35.537
I mean, what's going through your mind?

15:35.557 --> 15:36.739
Why do you have to have this stuff?

15:36.779 --> 15:41.484
Well, you know, I realized, especially when I, oh, let me tell you one other thing.

15:41.584 --> 15:42.705
I'll answer your question.

15:42.725 --> 15:52.296
So I'm talking to Phyllis on the phone, and I just sort of parenthetically say, by the way, where was that short story, time script, all these years?

15:52.817 --> 15:57.302
And she said, well, it was stuck between the pages of the time script of Green Hills of Africa.

15:59.628 --> 16:02.051
